# LESSON TWO: Types of Data

# Vocabulary

Integer - a positive or negative whole number
Float - any decimal number
String - any stretch of characters that are surrounded by "" OR ''
Boolean - a type of data that is true or false

# Types of Data Big Ideas: 

# Integers are whole numbers
>>> g = 9
>>> g = 9 + 1

# Floats are decimal numbers
>>> dollars = 10.23
>>> dollars = dollars + -10

# Strings are used for lots of things
>>>my_name = 'Mr. H'
>>>my_occupation = 'Teacher'
>>>my_hobbies = 'Programming'

# Booleans are useful, but not right now
>>>over_21 = True
>>>three_hundred_dollars = False

